			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Actually the damage ratio between the featherwood and the Stonewood are damn near exactly the same.  The only reason that people think the featherwood gets more headshots is because you shoot more arrows at the same mob.  With my featherwood on the mob i headshot about 95% of them somewhere between 100% and 1%.  With the Stonewood I often kill them outright before HS goes off on them so it seems like less speed but it is mostly the same killing ratio.
<br />

<br />
HS is a random chance and there is no way to increase that chance that I have been able to figure out other than, anything that will increase the number of times you actually hit the mob instead of missing, which will increase your HS occurances because you have to make a hit to be able to get a chance of HS going off.  So make sure your eagle Eye line of spells is up at all times.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=923184" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://www.outcastedrage.com/images/Lemback1.jpg" border="0" /></a>
<br />
~ Proud Officer of <a href="http://www.outcastedrage.com" target="_blank" class="postlink">Outcasted Rage</a> ~
<br />
~ 66 Hunter Ranger of Karana ~
<br />
~ Povar ~</span><span class="gentblsmall"></span></td>
