				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Sorry folks, really. The topic is about HEADSHOT and you want to teach the opener to trade in his Stonewood for a featherwood? Which definitely BREAKS ROOT?
<br />

<br />
Best bet would be primordial driftwood. Kinda useless proc, but it does NOT break roots. And its rather fast, so you may get more headshots then with stonewood.
<br />

<br />
Just one thing: Mobs in AC have high resistances for their level, so root maybe partially resistet at any time.
<br />

<br />
Another thing in AC: there are a lot of roamers in there. Try to shoot them first. Personally, I prefer zoning out if I get more then one add, just to break the Camp and save a lot of mana. Once done, you will be fine.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=825214" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://www.vielosofa.de/img/gemischtes/eq_sig_geadenea.jpg" border="0" /></a>
