			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I hunt often..well I should say I spend at least an hour everytime I am on hunting in AC. This is what I have found.
<br />

<br />
Snared mobs go down faster than rooted mobs with Head Shot. If you get as far away as you can from the mob.. snare it and start shooting.. the casters, for the most part, will stop short and start casting on you. Put up your cold and fire resist buffs. I let them cast all the want.. while I shoot at them. Once they get to close I will root them. But usually by that time they are close to turning and running anyway. Stonewood is a great bow for this. 
<br />

<br />
The damn blood guards are a pain. Root them right away and snare them. They seem to deflect or dodge or what ever the Head shot more than they others.. I figure it is because they are the warriors and probably have a higher armor class then the casters there fore are less likely to get Head shotted. Saying that.. I have taken them down with the first shot. 
<br />

<br />
I have gone there PLing some friends and a cleric friend would chain stun them and I would kill them. worked great.. another time I went with a Beast lord friend and his pet would tank. Boy they fell quick then. Heasdshot went off more frequently it seemed, especially if you can get behind the mob.
<br />

<br />
I also believe that if your pull shot is coming from the side or behind the mob, you will get a headshot more often. 
<br />

<br />
Just my 2cp on using HS in AC. GL and have fun. Destroy the words, ice shards, and the bones. Keep everything else and sell it. after an hour hunting there I can usually make about 1k in pp and then another 700 to 1k pp selling the acrylia in the bazaar. If you get the named ones up there gear will sell for 5k to 10k in the bazaar. Well atleast on Brell.<br />_________________<br />Hunter Kelsair Swiftarrow
<br />
Forest Stalker on Brell</span><span class="gentblsmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
